cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of accurately registering point clouds from a low-resolution sensor, which is a common problem in robotics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture for alignment using Gaussian Mixture Models, which involves designing a more robust energy function and efficiently convolving the two GMMs over the whole 3D space. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses error estimation and dual dynamic global probability alignment, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, indicating that it could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
